RACE.RACE_TEXT: CHURCHILL DOWNS RACE 1 1 1/16M Dirt CR: 80. Maiden Claiming Purse 42000. FOR MAIDENS, THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD. Three Year Olds, 118 lbs.; Older, 125 lbs. Claiming Price $20,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: RIVER IN EGYPT bobbled slightly upon leaving the gates, tracked along the inside, saved ground in pursuit of the leaders around the far turn, offered a rail bid approaching midstretch, led in the final furlong and edged away. REGIMENTAL broke half a beat slow, trailed while keen just off of the inside into the first turn, tugged closer while between horses in the three path down the backstretch, tracked in the four path around the far turn, took aim outside of the leaders entering the lane, bid in upper stretch, but was outkicked by a rail bidder in the final furlong. DIVINING STONE vied along the inside into the first turn before switching course outside of his outer counterpart around the first turn, pressed in the three path down the backstretch, gained an advantage at the half mile pole, led in the two path around the far turn as an outer rival sustained pressure, but was outkicked by a bidder on either side in midstretch, gave way in the final furlong, yet held show. REPREHEND broke a step slow and was last away, stalked outside of the top pair and from the four path around the first turn, bid outside of the new leader and from the three path around the far turn, vied turning for home, but yielded between horses in upper stretch. CRONUS raced at the rear in the four path, but failed to respond to urging in the five path around the far turn and played no factor. BON BUENO set the pace in the two path, but was headed by an outer rival at the half mile pole, faltered between horses entering the far turn, then was jogged home while distanced before walking off.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: CHURCHILL DOWNS RACE 2 5F Dirt CR: 86. Maiden Special Weight Purse 120000. FOR MAIDENS, TWO YEARS OLD. Weight, 119 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: GO OTTO GO leaned in slightly at the start before bobbling half a stride soon after, engaged the early leader from the outside approaching the turn, gained an advantage entering it, inched clear while well in hand leaving the five sixteenths marker, drew off with good energy when let out in upper stretch, then was put to wraps with the deal sealed in the final sixteenth. BEAUDACIOUS COLTON bumped with an outer rival at the start, chased the pace setters from the three path around the turn, ranged up turning for home, but quickly failed to keep pace with the leader in upper stretch, yet remained clear of show through the final furlong. LIBERAL ARTS broke a step slow while last away, trailed in the two path, split rivals while launching a rally in the five path in midstretch, and sustained a charge while shifting inwardly to gain show from an outer rival in the final sixteenth. FIFTH AVENUE hopped and bumped the inner half of the gate at the start, laid off of the pace in the three to four paths gained show at the furlong grounds, but lost that position to an inner rival in the closing stages. BERNIN HOT was a bit fractious loading, then propped at the start, lacked speed in the five to four path into the turn, then made little impact in the six path through the final furlong. SUGA STEVE broke through the starting gate pre-race, jogged for a quarter mile before reloading without further incident, broke sharply and cleared early on, met an outer challenge approaching the turn, got headed entering it, sustained inside pressure before giving way at the five sixteenths pole, and weakened through the final furlong. CASSIUS bumped with an inner rival at the start, tracked behind the leading pair from the two path, spun for home between horses, then faded through the final furlong. TECHNE balked loading, then became fractious in the starting gate, lacked speed in the four path, and was outrun turning for home.

UNSTOPPABLE ME bumped an outer rival at the start, got rank behind foes entering the first turn, settled into tracking stride around that bend, then weakened under urging around the far turn. SHAZIER was herded into an inner rival at the start, tracked in the three path, but weakened in the two path around the far turn.
